Quote:  I do not know Tommy Roundhead's Maori name, but there was a heavily tattooed Maori known to the whalers as Blueskin, and Blueskin Bay at Waitati was named after him, although Blueskin Beach at Goodwood was named because of a plant with berries with a blue skin. They were small and good to eat and were numerous there. The old chief at Blueskin Bay was very blue in his tattoo; ...
